Packagecom.splunk.services.events
Classpublic class ServiceErrorEvent
InheritanceServiceErrorEvent flash.events.ErrorEvent

An object dispatches a ServiceErrorEvent object when an error causes a service operation to fail.

Constructor detail
ServiceErrorEvent()constructor
public function ServiceErrorEvent(type:String, bubbles:Boolean = false, cancelable:Boolean = false, text:String = "", errorType:String = "", messages:Array = null)

Creates a new ServiceErrorEvent object that contains information about service error events.

Parameters
type:String — The type of the event.
 
bubbles:Boolean (default = false) — Determines whether the Event object participates in the bubbling stage of the event flow.
 
cancelable:Boolean (default = false) — Determines whether the Event object can be cancelled.
 
text:String (default = "") — Text to be displayed as an error message.
 
errorType:String (default = "") — The specific type of error that occurred.
 
messages:Array (default = null) — The list of SplunkMessage objects describing the error that occurred.

public override function toString():String

Returns a string that contains all the properties of this ServiceErrorEvent object. The string is in the following format:

[ServiceErrorEvent type=value bubbles=value cancelable=value eventPhase=value text=value errorType=value messages=value]

Constant detail
CONTROL_ERRORconstant
public static const CONTROL_ERROR:String = "controlError"

Defines the value of the type property of a controlError event object.

This event has the following properties:

PropertyValue
bubblesfalse
cancelablefalse; there is no default behavior to cancel.
currentTargetThe object that is actively processing the Event object with an event listener.
targetThe object experiencing a control error.
textText to be displayed as an error message.
errorTypeThe specific type of error that occurred.

public static const ERROR:String = "error"

Defines the value of the type property of an error event object.

This event has the following properties:

PropertyValue
bubblesfalse
cancelablefalse; there is no default behavior to cancel.
currentTargetThe object that is actively processing the Event object with an event listener.
targetThe object experiencing an error.
textText to be displayed as an error message.
errorTypeThe specific type of error that occurred.
